 \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"reports\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2149}, {\"ngram\": \"ministers\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2169}, {\"ngram\": \"any arrests\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2222}, {\"ngram\": \"the test\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in October 2023, a total of 65 British lawmakers joined the European Union in calling foran end to live facial recognition technology, which was outlawed in the first part of 2023.\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2302, \"end\": 2309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999792664906012, \"rank\": 1.9992753958309354e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2340, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999990694505, \"rank\": 8.439338367198623e-09, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"October\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2281}, {\"ngram\": \"a total\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2295}, {\"ngram\": \"foran end\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition technology\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2404}, {\"ngram\": \"the first part\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The British lawmakers joined several nonprofits and charitable groups in calling for using live face recognition to be discontinued.\", \"from\": 2452, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999792664906012, \"rank\": 1.9992753958309354e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"several nonprofits\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2499}, {\"ngram\": \"charitable groups\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"live face recognition\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among many others,Big Brother Watchhas already criticized facial recognition surveillance cameras in the UK for collecting millions of faceprints without permission and citing this as a dangerous precedent.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2691, \"end\": 2693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.972828090136583, \"rank\": 0.027930837722223434, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many others\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"Big Brother Watchhas\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2624}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition surveillance cameras\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2683}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2717}, {\"ngram\": \"faceprints\", \"from\": 2721, \"to\": 2731}, {\"ngram\": \"permission\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2750}, {\"ngram\": \"a dangerous precedent\", \"from\": 2770, \"to\": 2791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such technology was viewed as a danger to liberties and privacy.\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such technology\", \"from\": 2793, \"to\": 2808}, {\"ngram\": \"a danger\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2831}, {\"ngram\": \"liberties\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2844}, {\"ngram\": \"privacy\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it has not been enough to appease privacy advocacy Quadrature du N